President Obama announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. Kelvin Droegemeier was nominated for Member of the National Science Board, Maurice B. Foley was nominated for Judge of the United States Tax Court, and Dan Ashe was nominated for Director of the United States Fish and Wildlife Service. The President expressed confidence that these individuals would serve the American people well in their new roles and thanked them for agreeing to lend their talents to the administration. The article provides background information on each nominee's qualifications and experience.